Multilingual Perspectives
Insights from the 6th CICPE across languages and cultures

The 6th China International Consumer Products Expo was not only a showcase of global goods but also a meeting point of languages, cultures, and consumer behaviors. Engaging with exhibitors and attendees from Asia, Europe, and the Americas offered valuable multilingual perspectives on the future of consumption.

English – Many international brands emphasized sustainability, AI integration, and post-pandemic recovery strategies. Terms like "resilience," "traceability," and "carbon neutrality" appeared frequently in product descriptions and brand messaging.

中文 (Chinese) – Chinese exhibitors and livestream hosts focused on "精品" (boutique quality), "首发" (first launch), and "国潮" (national trend). The language of digital engagement — "直播带货" (livestream selling) and "私域流量" (private domain traffic) — dominated conversations about how brands reach younger consumers.

Español (Spanish) – Representatives from Latin American countries highlighted agricultural and organic consumer goods, using terms like "sostenibilidad" (sustainability) and "comercio justo" (fair trade). Their perspective underscored the growing demand for ethically sourced products in China's market.

Français (French) – French luxury and skincare brands spoke of "l'élégance durable" (sustainable elegance) and "innovation sensorielle" (sensory innovation), blending tradition with modern consumer expectations.

